Composition requirements:
- Make the slide feel like a NotebookLM-style whiteboard explainer, not a stock photo.
- Use hand-drawn black line art, simple business characters only when useful, arrows, boxed steps, doodle icons, charts, formulas, or metaphorical objects.
- Text must be large, clean, and readable at 1280x720.
- Keep the slide uncluttered: one main idea, 1-2 short text elements maximum unless the required text is a compact formula.
- Do not copy narration into the image. The visible text should be a short label or takeaway, not a sentence from the voiceover.
- Never use ellipses, trailing dots, cropped words, half-written text, fake text, placeholder text, tiny captions, or paragraph fragments.
- Every visible word must fit fully inside the canvas with generous margins.
- Avoid tiny labels, dense tables, small UI text, subtitles, paragraph text, and decorative micro-copy.
- Use soft accents sparingly: pastel pink, yellow marker highlight, teal, light green.
- Avoid photorealistic people, office stock imagery, tiny unreadable UI screens, dense paragraphs, and decorative filler.
- Do not include brand marks, NotebookLM logo, Open Notebook text, signatures, or watermarks.
- Do not include English words anywhere in the slide.
